T1  - Explaining International Fertility Differences*
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2009.124.2.771
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 124
IS  - 2
SP  - 771
EP  - 807
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Why do fertility rates vary so much across countries? Why are European fertility rates so much lower than American fertility rates? To answer these questions we extend the Barro—Becker framework to incorporate the decision to accumulate human capital (which determines earnings) and health capital (which determines life span). We find that cross-country differences in productivity and taxes go a long way toward explaining the observed differences in fertility and mortality.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2009.124.2.771
ER  - 



