TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dustmann, Christian
AU  - Ludsteck, Johannes
AU  - Schönberg, Uta
T1  - Revisiting the German Wage Structure*
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2009.124.2.843
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 124
IS  - 2
SP  - 843
EP  - 881
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper shows that wage inequality in West Germany has increased over the past three decades, contrary to common perceptions. During the 1980s, the increase was concentrated at the top of the distribution; in the 1990s, it occurred at the bottom end as well. Our findings are consistent with the view that both in Germany and in the United States, technological change is responsible for the widening of the wage distribution at the top. At the bottom of the wage distribution, the increase in inequality is better explained by episodic events, such as supply shocks and changes in labor market institutions. These events happened a decade later in Germany than in the United States.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2009.124.2.843
ER  - 



